This change fixes support for intellisense with phpstorm.

I found a number of open tickets for phpstorm to get class_alias working correctly, but they date back many years. So I don't know what the deal with it is.
- adds a new file `deprecated.php` which contains all the aliases (for easier management).
- aliased classes are now have a stub class.

The stub looks like this.

```
namespace Cake\Network\Email;

if (false) {
    /**
     * @deprecated Use Cake\Mailer\Email instead
     */
    class Email extends \Cake\Mailer\Email
    {

    }
}
```

It's a do nothing chunk of code that tells the IDE to mark the old classes as deprecated. So they are now shown with a dashed highlight to indicate it's deprecated.

